Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.87,0:00:25.12,apollon main,Sen,0000,0000,0000,,Like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.12,0:00:26.04,apollon main,Photography Club,0000,0000,0000,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.04,0:00:28.69,apollon main,Girl,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, when did you two become friends?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.69,0:00:30.81,apollon main,Girl,0000,0000,0000,,Where do you practice?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.81,0:00:33.06,apollon main,Girl,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}How do you play in such perfect unison?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.84,0:00:35.47,apollon main,Kaoru,0000,0000,0000,,Sen, let's get out of here. \NWhen I count to five, run left.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.06,0:00:35.47,apollon main,Girl,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}You don't have to hide anything from us!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.80,0:00:37.47,apollon main,Girl,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Tell us!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.96,0:00:36.81,apollon main,Kaoru,0000,0000,0000,,Five.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.81,0:00:37.47,apollon main,Kaoru,0000,0000,0000,,Four.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.83,0:00:38.94,apollon main,Kaoru,0000,0000,0000,,Three.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.94,0:00:39.83,apollon main,Kaoru,0000,0000,0000,,Two.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.83,0:00:40.47,apollon main,Kaoru,0000,0000,0000,,One.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.56,0:00:42.43,apollon main,Photography Club,0000,0000,0000,,They're running off again!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.77,0:00:43.18,apollon main,Kaoru,0000,0000,0000,,Ri!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.49,0:00:48.48,apollon main,Girl 2,0000,0000,0000,,Aw, come on! Where are you going?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.69,0:00:53.08,apollon main,Yamaoka,0000,0000,0000,,Shit. The girls were supposed \Nto be chasing after us.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.08,0:00:56.24,apollon main,Yamaoka,0000,0000,0000,,Right now, those guys are just like The Beatles!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.24,0:00:58.47,apollon main,Seiji,0000,0000,0000,,I've learned from them.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.47,0:01:01.24,apollon main,Seiji,0000,0000,0000,,Forget about next year's festival.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.24,0:01:04.15,apollon main,Seiji,0000,0000,0000,,I'm looking even further ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.15,0:01:07.73,apollon main,Seiji,0000,0000,0000,,I'll go so far that they'll \Nnever be able to catch up.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.90,0:02:43.76,apollon main,Kaoru,0000,0000,0000,,Pops! Sorry I haven't been coming recently.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.22,0:02:48.00,apollon main,Kaoru,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? He's not here. Maybe in the basement?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.00,0:02:49.60,apollon main,Kaoru,0000,0000,0000,,Sen, what's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.83,0:02:56.11,apollon main,Sen,0000,0000,0000,,Richie, would you check to see if Jun's down there?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.38,0:02:57.93,apollon main,Kaoru,0000,0000,0000,,What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.93,0:03:00.92,apollon main,Kaoru,0000,0000,0000,,It's not summer vacation, \Nso why would he be{\fscx350}-
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.92,0:03:04.73,apollon main,Dad,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, a lot's happened while \Nyou boys weren't around.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.73,0:03:08.00,apollon main,Dad,0000,0000,0000,,But he's not here now. He left last week.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.92,0:03:12.58,apollon main,Dad,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, I haven't seen you in a long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.58,0:03:13.50,apollon main,Kaoru,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.41,0:03:16.25,apollon main,Dad,0000,0000,0000,,I've been waiting for you, Richie-rich.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.93,0:03:20.54,apollon main,Dad,0000,0000,0000,,My piano trio is finally together again!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.06,0:03:28.02,apollon main,Dad,0000,0000,0000,,Junichi was disowned by his father \Nright after he came back this summer.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.41,0:03:29.76,apollon main,Kaoru,0000,0000,0000,,Disowned?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.76,0:03:32.82,apollon main,Dad,0000,0000,0000,,Well, first he went against his parents' \Nwishes by going to college in Tokyo,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.82,0:03:35.89,apollon main,Dad,0000,0000,0000,,but then he stopped going to school
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.89,0:03:38.90,apollon main,Dad,0000,0000,0000,,and got wrapped up in political activism.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.29,0:03:42.47,apollon main,Dad,0000,0000,0000,,When the prodigal son wandered back home,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.47,0:03:45.16,apollon main,Dad,0000,0000,0000,,it's no wonder his dad was furious.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.63,0:03:48.50,apollon main,Dad,0000,0000,0000,,He wasn't allowed to set foot in his family's house,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.50,0:03:53.67,apollon main,Dad,0000,0000,0000,,and soon after, I ran into him at the bar, three sheets to the wind,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.67,0:03:55.84,apollon main,Dad,0000,0000,0000,,so I let him take refuge here.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.66,0:03:57.59,apollon main,Sen,0000,0000,0000,,Pops...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.97,0:04:01.91,apollon main,Sen,0000,0000,0000,,Did he leave because of me?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.91,0:04:06.35,apollon main,Dad,0000,0000,0000,,No, no. He happened to \Nfind a cheap room to rent.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.06,0:04:08.38,apollon main,Dad,0000,0000,0000,,It's not your fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.38,0:04:10.06,apollon main,Sen,0000,0000,0000,,But I...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.35,0:04:16.41,apollon main,Kaoru,0000,0000,0000,,Sentaro!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.72,0:04:19.68,apollon main,Kaoru,0000,0000,0000,,Do not mope your life away!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.68,0:04:24.36,apollon main,Kaoru,0000,0000,0000,,Playing one good session will drive \Naway those blues, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.04,0:04:30.08,apollon main,Kaoru,0000,0000,0000,,Never mind! Forget I did that!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.83,0:04:35.38,apollon main,Sen,0000,0000,0000,,I get it, Mr. Bill Evans, I get it!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.14,0:04:39.63,apollon main,Sen,0000,0000,0000,,All right! What do you say we play a session \Nso I can work off this gloominess?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.31,0:04:50.47,apollon main,Yukari,0000,0000,0000,,Junichi?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.31,0:04:54.85,apollon main,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.33,0:05:00.27,apollon main,Yukari,0000,0000,0000,,Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.61,0:05:02.86,apollon main,Yukari,0000,0000,0000,,Don't ignore me!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.12,0:05:14.79,apollon main,Yukari,0000,0000,0000,,What made him change this much?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.95,0:05:19.83,apollon main,Yukari,0000,0000,0000,,That one winter day, in the \Nbasement... What was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.91,0:05:24.98,apollon main,Yukari,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Did he just do it on a whim?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.14,0:05:45.12,apollon main,Yukari,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Even if I knock, he may not open the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.00,0:05:54.90,apollon main,Yukari,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Or would he look at me again \Nwith those vacant eyes?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.97,0:06:04.42,apollon main,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, but that doesn't suit you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.08,0:06:14.40,apollon main,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,You win. That angry face of \Nyours is my Achilles heel.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.02,0:06:18.31,apollon main,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,You had that same expression \Nwhen we first met.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.31,0:06:19.52,apollon main,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,I remember it well.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.45,0:06:28.24,apollon main,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,What are you gonna do? Just go home? Or...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.37,0:06:44.84,apollon main,Girl A,0000,0000,0000,,Mukae!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.05,0:06:49.85,apollon main,Girl A,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me. Would you give this to Nishimi?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.79,0:06:54.36,apollon main,Ritsuko,0000,0000,0000,,Um, wouldn't it be better if \Nyou gave it to him yourself?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.36,0:06:58.67,apollon main,Girl A,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I couldn't! I'd be \Ntoo nervous! So, please!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.80,0:07:00.86,apollon main,Girl,0000,0000,0000,,You did it!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.00,0:07:04.86,apollon main,Kaoru,0000,0000,0000,,For me?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.16,0:07:09.61,apollon main,Ritsuko,0000,0000,0000,,It's been a while since the festival, but \Nyour popularity hasn't waned, Kaoru.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.62,0:07:11.58,apollon main,Kaoru,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.90,0:07:28.92,apollon main,Ritsuko,0000,0000,0000,,What am I staring at?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.92,0:07:32.75,apollon main,Ritsuko,0000,0000,0000,,Am I jealous? It has nothing to do with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.75,0:07:34.05,apollon main,Tokie,0000,0000,0000,,Ri!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.39,0:07:37.61,apollon main,Tokie,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, which scarf design \Ndo you think is better?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.77,0:07:42.66,apollon main,Tokie,0000,0000,0000,,Actually, there's this guy I kind of like,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.66,0:07:45.16,apollon main,Tokie,0000,0000,0000,,and I'm thinking about making one for him.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.16,0:07:46.18,apollon main,Ritsuko,0000,0000,0000,,Who is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.18,0:07:48.08,apollon main,Tokie,0000,0000,0000,,I can't say yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.08,0:07:50.29,apollon main,Tokie,0000,0000,0000,,But how about you, Ri?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.29,0:07:52.91,apollon main,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't there someone you wanna knit for?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.91,0:07:55.41,apollon main,Tokie,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, let's knit together!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.74,0:07:59.86,apollon main,Ritsuko,0000,0000,0000,,But I don't have anyone to give it to.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.86,0:08:03.32,apollon main,Tokie,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, be honest with yourself, Ri.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.32,0:08:06.54,apollon main,Tokie,0000,0000,0000,,Just now, you were staring \Nat a certain someone.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.51,0:08:10.01,apollon main,Ritsuko,0000,0000,0000,,It's not what you think. \NDon't get the wrong idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.01,0:08:14.80,apollon main,Tokie,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, yeah. Nishimi \Nis just a friend, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.19,0:08:17.27,apollon main,Tokie,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry! I'll be back!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.30,0:08:23.63,apollon main,Ritsuko,0000,0000,0000,,What a beautiful color.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.31,0:08:26.66,apollon main,Ritsuko,0000,0000,0000,,I bet Kaoru would look good in this.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.58,0:08:32.57,apollon main,Ritsuko,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Wait a second.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.53,0:08:36.04,apollon main,Ritsuko,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong with me?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.04,0:08:38.34,apollon main,,0000,0000,0000,,Why is my heart beating so fast?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.80,0:08:43.34,apollon main,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,That day in the basement?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.34,0:08:46.52,apollon main,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, yeah. I almost forgot about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.65,0:08:49.97,apollon main,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,You wanna know why I did it?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.97,0:08:54.09,apollon main,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,Was it a little too stimulating for you?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.59,0:08:58.00,apollon main,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry. I was just feeling kind \Nof mischievous at the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.50,0:09:03.35,apollon main,Yurika,0000,0000,0000,,N-No!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.62,0:09:05.87,apollon main,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.87,0:09:08.11,apollon main,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't you come in here because \Nyou wanted me to do this?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.45,0:09:12.36,apollon main,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,What were you hoping for? \NA declaration of love?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.64,0:09:15.13,apollon main,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry to disappoint you, young lady.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.13,0:09:17.38,apollon main,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,But this is the kind of guy I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.85,0:09:25.35,apollon main,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,You've stopped fighting back.\NAre you resigned to it already?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.91,0:09:26.55,apollon main,Yurika,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.62,0:09:30.80,apollon main,Yurika,0000,0000,0000,,"If I act like this, \Nshe'll probably run off."
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.70,0:09:33.01,apollon main,Yurika,0000,0000,0000,,Is that what you're thinking?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.51,0:09:37.76,apollon main,Yurika,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not afraid of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.40,0:09:40.26,apollon main,Yurika,0000,0000,0000,,You can do what you want with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.89,0:09:44.96,apollon main,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.33,0:09:49.71,apollon main,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,Go home. Don't ever come back here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.71,0:09:53.16,apollon main,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not the same person I was before.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.16,0:09:57.03,apollon main,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,I dropped out of college, and my family disowned me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.34,0:10:01.99,apollon main,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,Society gave me the boot, and \Nthere's no way for me to get back.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.63,0:10:06.00,apollon main,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,Get close to me and your life will be ruined too.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.85,0:10:09.57,apollon main,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,If you understand what I'm sayin', \Nget the hell out of here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.68,0:10:22.64,apollon main,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.07,0:10:26.39,apollon main,Yurika,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sick of you calling me "young lady,"
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.39,0:10:29.39,apollon main,Yurika,0000,0000,0000,,so I thought I'd get rid of that image you have of me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.69,0:10:33.42,apollon main,Yurika,0000,0000,0000,,If you're not the same person you once were,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.15,0:10:38.08,apollon main,Yurika,0000,0000,0000,,then I can become a new person too.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.38,0:10:46.60,apollon main,Muroi,0000,0000,0000,,Katsuragi, I'm gonna become a new me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.60,0:10:47.96,apollon main,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,Don't!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.08,0:10:56.21,apollon main,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,Don't go throwing away something \Nprecious for someone like me.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.24,0:11:09.06,apollon main,Arita,0000,0000,0000,,So you're the Katsuragi \NI've heard so much about.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.69,0:11:13.09,apollon main,Arita,0000,0000,0000,,How about saying something \Nto mark the occasion?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.09,0:11:13.94,apollon main,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,Me?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.57,0:11:17.19,apollon main,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,I'm just passing through,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.76,0:11:22.32,apollon main,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,but I'd like to share my opinion on \Nwhat a college {\i1}should{\i0\fscx150} {\fscx100}be like.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.11,0:11:26.95,apollon main,Muroi,0000,0000,0000,,Katsuragi... You inspired me.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.10,0:11:30.05,apollon main,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,Muroi, you...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.05,0:11:32.25,apollon main,Muroi,0000,0000,0000,,Listening to your speech made \Nme feel ashamed of myself
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.25,0:11:36.35,apollon main,Muroi,0000,0000,0000,,for doing nothing but studying for exams and playing music.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.92,0:11:41.43,apollon main,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\bord0\shad0\blur1.15\fs29\fnBarbedorT\frz349.25\frx348\fry334\org(478,593)\pos(356,598)}The Decline of a False System
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.43,0:11:46.44,apollon main,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\c&H2B2D32&\blur1.15\bord0\shad0\fs30\frx16\fry2\frz11.732\pos(750,331)}Strike Against\N Rising Tuition
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.44,0:11:46.44,apollon main,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur1.15\bord0\shad0\fs30\c&H050A0A&\frx0\fry10\frz347.463\pos(183,631)}All Students on Strike
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.10,0:11:46.44,apollon main,Muroi,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Katsuragi, in the next battle, \Nif something were to happen to me,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.15,0:11:50.81,apollon main,Muroi,0000,0000,0000,,would you take over for me, even just for a little while?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.24,0:11:53.79,apollon main,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,Arita, I...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.16,0:12:04.34,apollon main,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Muroi. Come over once \Nin a while to play the sax.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.36,0:12:10.20,apollon main,Muroi,0000,0000,0000,,Katsuragi! Arita's been arrested!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.51,0:12:22.67,apollon main,Muroi,0000,0000,0000,,The bones are shattered,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.42,0:12:25.90,apollon main,Muroi,0000,0000,0000,,so the doc told me my fingers won't \Nbe able to move like they used to.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.90,0:12:28.28,apollon main,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What about the sax?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.28,0:12:29.69,apollon main,Muroi,0000,0000,0000,,I can't play anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.99,0:12:33.62,apollon main,Muroi,0000,0000,0000,,Don't look so glum, Katsuragi.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.62,0:12:37.31,apollon main,Muroi,0000,0000,0000,,Now I can dump everything I don't \Nneed and just focus on the movement.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.68,0:12:41.15,apollon main,Muroi,0000,0000,0000,,I'm gonna become a new me.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.35,0:12:49.83,apollon main,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,What am I doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.98,0:12:52.33,apollon main,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Katsuragi?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.33,0:12:53.88,apollon main,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.88,0:12:54.84,apollon main,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Where are you going?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.34,0:13:08.65,apollon main,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,I don't wanna see any more people \Nget hurt because of me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.44,0:13:16.74,apollon main,Yukari,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know what happened to you, \Nand I don't intend to ask about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.71,0:13:22.11,apollon main,Yukari,0000,0000,0000,,But I can see that you're hurt deeply.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.78,0:13:27.20,apollon main,Yukari,0000,0000,0000,,Can't I support you?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.65,0:13:31.45,apollon main,Yukari,0000,0000,0000,,Am I being too pushy?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.01,0:13:37.58,apollon main,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.69,0:13:41.59,apollon main,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,You're a pushy woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.86,0:14:00.31,apollon main,Sen,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Maybe I should stop takin' naps on the roof.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.98,0:14:03.37,apollon main,Girl 1,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Hey, wasn't that Yurika?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.37,0:14:05.75,apollon main,Girl 1,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Was she called in by the teacher again?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.75,0:14:08.82,apollon main,Girl 2,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Yeah. Yurika's been acting weird these days.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.02,0:14:11.06,apollon main,Girl 2,0000,0000,0000,,She's totally changed.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.06,0:14:13.91,apollon main,Girl 2,0000,0000,0000,,What happened to that innocence she used to have?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.91,0:14:15.86,apollon main,Girl 1,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe something happened to her?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.86,0:14:18.92,apollon main,Girl 2,0000,0000,0000,,I asked her that, but she wouldn't answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.92,0:14:23.00,apollon main,Girl 1,0000,0000,0000,,Well, since she cut her hair \Nlike that, could it mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.26,0:14:24.34,apollon main,Girl 1,0000,0000,0000,,she's got a broken heart?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.78,0:14:28.38,apollon main,Sen,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.82,0:14:30.12,apollon main,Sen,0000,0000,0000,,What'd he do to her?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.61,0:14:33.64,apollon main,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,So you're Sentaro, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.06,0:14:35.40,apollon main,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,Do you like jazz?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.20,0:14:42.15,apollon main,Sen,0000,0000,0000,,Jun has been like a brother to me ever since I first met him.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.02,0:14:45.15,apollon main,Sen,0000,0000,0000,,I wanted to get good at jazz like him.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.64,0:14:46.76,apollon main,Sen,0000,0000,0000,,Be strong like him.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.76,0:14:48.65,apollon main,Sen,0000,0000,0000,,Become cool like him.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.19,0:14:52.16,apollon main,Sen,0000,0000,0000,,I tried to follow in his footsteps \Nevery step of the way,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.88,0:14:55.49,apollon main,Sen,0000,0000,0000,,thinking I'd catch up someday.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.49,0:14:56.79,apollon main,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Sen-boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.20,0:15:00.64,apollon main,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,Your woman forgot something.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.97,0:15:09.76,apollon main,Sen,0000,0000,0000,,If he would just talk to me, maybe I'd understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.17,0:15:16.60,apollon main,Sen,0000,0000,0000,,But if he did something to {\i1}her{\i0}, I'll...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.04,0:15:25.23,apollon main,Sen,0000,0000,0000,,J-Jun!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.30,0:15:27.48,apollon main,Sen,0000,0000,0000,,I need to talk to...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.32,0:15:33.95,apollon main,Sen,0000,0000,0000,,Son of a...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.95,0:15:35.45,apollon main,Sen,0000,0000,0000,,bitch!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.74,0:15:43.13,apollon main,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,Shit. He's the one person I didn't \Nwant to find out about this.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.13,0:15:45.09,apollon main,Yurika,0000,0000,0000,,But what else could you do?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.74,0:15:48.84,apollon main,Yurika,0000,0000,0000,,He was bound to find out sooner or later.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.28,0:15:55.10,apollon main,Sen,0000,0000,0000,,I knew it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.98,0:15:58.60,apollon main,Sen,0000,0000,0000,,I knew she was beyond my \Nreach from the start.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.89,0:16:02.54,apollon main,Sen,0000,0000,0000,,I knew it. Or I thought I did, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.07,0:16:17.78,apollon main,Ritsuko,0000,0000,0000,,I don't understand myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.57,0:16:21.52,apollon main,Ritsuko,0000,0000,0000,,When I'm with Kaoru,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.52,0:16:25.00,apollon main,Ritsuko,0000,0000,0000,,I can really feel at ease \Nand have a good time.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.61,0:16:30.14,apollon main,Ritsuko,0000,0000,0000,,No. I decided long ago on \Nthe person that I like...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.26,0:16:33.76,apollon main,Kaoru,0000,0000,0000,,Hi, Ri.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.88,0:16:36.76,apollon main,Kaoru,0000,0000,0000,,Is Sen here?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.54,0:16:40.02,apollon main,Ritsuko,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I think so.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.11,0:16:45.62,apollon main,Kaoru,0000,0000,0000,,Knitting? Why would she bother hiding that?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.46,0:17:06.79,apollon main,Kaoru,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Sen!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.75,0:17:12.01,apollon main,Kaoru,0000,0000,0000,,Sen! What happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.96,0:17:16.59,apollon main,Sen,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.08,0:17:21.20,apollon main,Kaoru,0000,0000,0000,,You're obviously acting strangely \Ntoday. Tell me about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.77,0:17:24.04,apollon main,Sen,0000,0000,0000,,I saw 'em.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.04,0:17:24.98,apollon main,Kaoru,0000,0000,0000,,Who?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.40,0:17:28.86,apollon main,Sen,0000,0000,0000,,When I went to Jun's apartment, she was there.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.87,0:17:33.44,apollon main,Kaoru,0000,0000,0000,,Y-You're sure you saw her?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.44,0:17:33.99,apollon main,Sen,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.56,0:17:38.20,apollon main,Sen,0000,0000,0000,,And of all people, it had to be him.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.20,0:17:39.91,apollon main,Sen,0000,0000,0000,,That's what hurts the most.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.78,0:17:43.60,apollon main,Sen,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, it's done.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.60,0:17:45.04,apollon main,Sen,0000,0000,0000,,There's nothin' I can do.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.08,0:17:49.54,apollon main,Kaoru,0000,0000,0000,,You've still got it good.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.27,0:17:54.61,apollon main,Kaoru,0000,0000,0000,,Even though you were jilted, you've \Nstill got someone who cares for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.61,0:17:56.30,apollon main,Kaoru,0000,0000,0000,,It's like they say, you can't \Nsee the forest for the trees.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.21,0:18:02.35,apollon main,Kaoru,0000,0000,0000,,And those trees are so tall, you must \Nnot be able to see a damn thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.96,0:18:06.21,apollon main,Kaoru,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't you try looking more carefully?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.21,0:18:08.70,apollon main,Kaoru,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't it high time you realized it?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.70,0:18:10.36,apollon main,Sen,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What're you talkin' about?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.86,0:18:13.36,apollon main,Kaoru,0000,0000,0000,,Figure it out for yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.82,0:18:20.27,apollon main,Kaoru,0000,0000,0000,,I told him.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.27,0:18:21.45,apollon main,Ritsuko,0000,0000,0000,,Kaoru?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.95,0:18:24.79,apollon main,Ritsuko,0000,0000,0000,,You just got here and you're leaving already?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.62,0:18:27.40,apollon main,Kaoru,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. I've got something to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.07,0:18:29.50,apollon main,Kaoru,0000,0000,0000,,Are you done knitting for today?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.40,0:18:34.30,apollon main,Kaoru,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry. I couldn't help glancing at it before.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.08,0:18:38.26,apollon main,Kaoru,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure he'll like it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.74,0:18:43.10,apollon main,Kaoru,0000,0000,0000,,Ri, you're blushing! \NWas I right on the money?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.10,0:18:44.74,apollon main,Kaoru,0000,0000,0000,,Well, see you tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.37,0:18:48.10,apollon main,Ritsuko,0000,0000,0000,,Wait a min{\fscx350}-
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.40,0:18:55.28,apollon main,Kaoru,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure this is for the best.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.65,0:18:59.65,apollon main,Kaoru,0000,0000,0000,,Don't have a relapse! \NThis doesn't hurt at all!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.27,0:19:06.95,apollon main,Dad,0000,0000,0000,,I won't have it!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.47,0:19:09.66,apollon main,Dad,0000,0000,0000,,You and this man from God knows where...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.56,0:19:13.88,apollon main,Dad,0000,0000,0000,,Yurika, you're being tricked.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.20,0:19:16.95,apollon main,Yurika,0000,0000,0000,,What do you know, Father?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.95,0:19:22.26,apollon main,Dad,0000,0000,0000,,Shut your mouth! I'll bring home a \Nsuitable partner for you before long.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.26,0:19:27.36,apollon main,Dad,0000,0000,0000,,So don't meet with this man again, \NYurika. Do you understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.52,0:19:33.87,apollon main,Mom,0000,0000,0000,,Yurika, your father is just \Ntalking to you like that
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.87,0:19:35.57,apollon main,Mom,0000,0000,0000,,because he's worried about you!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.05,0:19:41.82,apollon main,Mom,0000,0000,0000,,You're a girl, so you have to \Ntake better care of yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.22,0:19:46.67,apollon main,Mom,0000,0000,0000,,Just in case, keep next Saturday open, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.67,0:19:49.45,apollon main,Mom,0000,0000,0000,,I made an appointment for \Nyou at the gynecologist.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.46,0:20:00.97,apollon main,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\c&H000209&\bord0\shad0\blur.5\fs35\fnBeautiful Every Time\an7\pos(248,97)\frz22.083}Are you eating properly? \NA letter came for you, so I'm \Nforwarding it on. \NLove, Mom
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.51,0:20:09.52,apollon main,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\c&H000000&\bord0\shad0\fnRaysHand\blur0.5\frz338.882\pos(709,85)}To My Comrade,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.51,0:20:09.52,apollon main,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\c&H000000&\bord0\shad0\fnRaysHand\blur0.5\frz338.882\pos(737,147)}from Isao Arita
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.74,0:20:22.28,apollon main,Sen,0000,0000,0000,,Richie, that rat. Throws out hints, then goes home...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.46,0:20:27.08,apollon main,Sen,0000,0000,0000,,Someone who cares for me? Like my family?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.31,0:20:28.73,apollon main,Sen,0000,0000,0000,,Is that what he meant?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.69,0:20:33.74,apollon main,Ritsuko,0000,0000,0000,,So you're gonna be the Virgin Mary
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.74,0:20:36.35,apollon main,Ritsuko,0000,0000,0000,,in the Christmas Nativity play, huh, Sa?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.35,0:20:39.38,apollon main,Sachiko,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. But I'm nervous about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.82,0:20:41.79,apollon main,Ritsuko,0000,0000,0000,,Hashiguchi will be there to see you too,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.79,0:20:43.05,apollon main,Ritsuko,0000,0000,0000,,so you have to do your best, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.05,0:20:45.72,apollon main,Sachiko,0000,0000,0000,,D-Don't mention him! I don't care if he...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.72,0:20:49.39,apollon main,Kota,0000,0000,0000,,Sis, you're the one that said you're \Ngonna marry him when you grow up!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.95,0:20:53.07,apollon main,Sachiko,0000,0000,0000,,What?! That was a long time ago!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.36,0:20:58.07,apollon main,Ritsuko,0000,0000,0000,,Um, Sentaro, I...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.07,0:21:02.03,apollon main,Ritsuko,0000,0000,0000,,When I grow up, I wanna get married.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.69,0:21:07.52,apollon main,Kaoru,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't it high time you realized it?
